03/07/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Regular bilateral talks between Macedonian and US defence officials took place Wednesday (2 July) at the Military Academy in Skopje. In addition to senior defence sector officials from the two countries, US Ambassador to Macedonia Lawrence Butler, Macedonian Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski and Chief of General Staff Lt Gen Metodi Stamboliski participated. Buckovski thanked Washington for its support and assistance, adding that $12m in US assistance this year would go towards special forces, improving the mobility of units and installing IT systems compatible with NATO standards. (MIA, Makfax - 02/07/03)
